    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-09-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-09-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1022"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1022">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Duke <persName
                            type="to">de Arcos</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-09-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 17, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 114.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 12th instant, in which you transmit an expression of the deep
                    sympathy felt by His Majesty’s Government and by Her Majesty the Queen Regent in
                    view of the terrible disaster in Texas.</p>
                <pb facs="0989" n="891" xml:id="pg_891"/>
                <p>Your note has been communicated to the President, who charges me to express his
                    sincere appreciation of the sympathetic, message transmitted by your
                    Government.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
